(40, 21, 19, 42, 13, 6, 9, NULL, 'Fig Tree Symbolism in Scripture', 'Both passages emphasize the expectation of fruit from a fig tree. In Matthew, the tree is cursed for bearing no fruit, while in Luke, there is a plea for patience before it is cut down. This connection highlights the theme of accountability for spiritual fruitfulness.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
